WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.260 --> 00:00:03.508
Praised be Jesus and Mary, everyone.

00:00:03.508 --> 00:00:09.354
A few years ago, I was sitting in
these pews, listening to catecheses.

00:00:09.354 --> 00:00:15.200
Today, for the first time, I have
the opportunity to speak about Saint

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:18.348
Anthony, the saint of the whole world.

00:00:18.348 --> 00:00:21.946
We are in the Basilica of Saint Anthony.

00:00:21.946 --> 00:00:26.443
To your right are the first-class
relics of Saint Anthony.

00:00:26.443 --> 00:00:30.940
It would be appropriate to say
something about Saint Anthony.

00:00:31.960 --> 00:00:38.494
But before we start talking about
Saint Anthony, considering that I

00:00:38.494 --> 00:00:45.029
manage a lot of YouTube content and
often delete inappropriate comments

00:00:45.029 --> 00:00:52.158
or insults, I occasionally come across
comments, which I believe are from

00:00:52.158 --> 00:00:58.098
either Protestants or perhaps Catholics
who have rejected Catholic doctrine.

00:00:58.098 --> 00:01:05.821
They call us idolaters, claiming that we
worship idols, referring, of course, to

00:01:05.821 --> 00:01:09.979
the saints and the Blessed Virgin Mary.

00:01:10.560 --> 00:01:15.678
First of all, I would like
to make a distinction between

00:01:15.678 --> 00:01:19.865
veneration and worship, because
there is a significant difference.

00:01:19.865 --> 00:01:25.448
In the Catholic Church, we venerate
the saints, we honor the saints.

00:01:25.448 --> 00:01:30.566
The Catechism of the Catholic Church
provides two reasons for this.

00:01:30.566 --> 00:01:38.011
First, because we see in them an example
of how the Lord worked, how God's grace

00:01:38.011 --> 00:01:44.525
operated, and they cooperated with God's
grace, serving as a model for us today.

00:01:44.525 --> 00:01:49.645
And the second thing is that
they are our intercessors.

00:01:49.645 --> 00:01:56.813
If today we can pray for one another
and believe that such prayers are

00:01:56.813 --> 00:02:03.982
heard, imagine the power of a saint's
prayer who is with God in heaven.

00:02:03.982 --> 00:02:09.614
As for worship, worship is
reserved only for God, the Triune

00:02:09.614 --> 00:02:12.175
God—Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.

00:02:12.175 --> 00:02:17.988
And so, that is one significant
difference if you find yourself in

00:02:17.988 --> 00:02:22.833
a discussion, to actually understand
the difference between worship, which

00:02:22.833 --> 00:02:26.224
is for God, and veneration of saints.

00:02:26.224 --> 00:02:29.131
Let's get back to the topic.

00:02:29.131 --> 00:02:32.038
Saint Anthony is a great saint.

00:02:32.038 --> 00:02:37.367
In fact, he is called the
saint of the whole world.

00:02:37.367 --> 00:02:44.635
And today's talk about Saint Anthony,
we can say the first image that comes to

00:02:44.635 --> 00:02:51.417
mind when we think of Saint Anthony, or
in Dalmatia Ante, in Herzegovina Ante,

00:02:51.417 --> 00:02:58.685
in Bosnia Anto, in Italy Antonio, the
first image of Anthony is that of keys.

00:02:59.605 --> 00:03:06.060
I believe that everyone has lost either
keys or some item and immediately

00:03:06.060 --> 00:03:09.039
thinks, let's pray to Saint Anthony.

00:03:09.039 --> 00:03:12.515
Another image of Saint
Anthony is miracles.

00:03:12.515 --> 00:03:16.487
Saint Anthony is actually
the saint of miracles.

00:03:16.487 --> 00:03:21.949
He performed miracles during his
lifetime, and even more so today.

00:03:21.949 --> 00:03:28.404
There are many testimonies from young
people and other believers who have come

00:03:28.404 --> 00:03:31.880
to this Basilica, especially on the 13th.

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:35.262
Pilgrimages to St.
Anthony with various vows.

00:03:35.262 --> 00:03:39.127
And they truly received
answers to their prayers.

00:03:39.127 --> 00:03:45.891
Another image of St. Anthony is the
lilies, and you can see the basilica's

00:03:45.891 --> 00:03:51.688
crest above, "florete quasi lilium,"
which means "bloom like lilies." If we

00:03:51.688 --> 00:03:59.419
look at this and all these images, I
would dare to say that they are somewhat

00:03:59.419 --> 00:04:05.700
sentimental because it is much easier
for us to relate to something simple.

00:04:06.255 --> 00:04:12.406
And so we turn to Saint Anthony
when we need help finding keys or

00:04:12.406 --> 00:04:17.678
for a quick prayer before an exam,
and Saint Anthony will assist.

00:04:17.678 --> 00:04:22.950
But behind the image of Saint
Anthony lies a difficult life, a

00:04:22.950 --> 00:04:25.587
life of suffering, we could say.

00:04:25.587 --> 00:04:31.738
Additionally, he was a great intellectual,
a Doctor of the Church, and a profound

00:04:31.738 --> 00:04:33.935
scholar of the Holy Scriptures.

00:04:35.450 --> 00:04:40.634
If I were to ask you here, who
prays to Saint Anthony, I believe

00:04:40.634 --> 00:04:42.485
everyone would raise their hand.

00:04:42.485 --> 00:04:47.299
But if I asked how well you
know the life of Saint Anthony,

00:04:47.299 --> 00:04:49.520
probably fewer hands would go up.

00:04:49.520 --> 00:04:53.594
I'll briefly say something about his
life, actually about the beginning

00:04:53.594 --> 00:04:58.778
of his life because my topic is the
calling of Saint Anthony, and we

00:04:58.778 --> 00:05:01.370
will only touch on the early parts.

00:05:02.135 --> 00:05:08.716
Saint Anthony was born in 1195 in
Lisbon to a wealthy noble family

00:05:08.716 --> 00:05:15.297
and, while still young, joined the
order of the Canons Regular of St.

00:05:15.297 --> 00:05:17.322
Augustine, or the Augustinians.

00:05:17.322 --> 00:05:24.409
He had the opportunity to study well,
truly delving into the Holy Scriptures and

00:05:24.409 --> 00:05:27.447
reaching an admirable level of knowledge.

00:05:27.447 --> 00:05:32.510
But it seemed that this
was not enough for him.

00:05:34.300 --> 00:05:39.156
Saint Anthony, while still
very young, heard about the

00:05:39.156 --> 00:05:44.553
Franciscans, the first Franciscans
who gave their lives in Morocco.

00:05:44.553 --> 00:05:52.108
This was, of course, in the 12th or
13th century, where they gave their

00:05:52.108 --> 00:05:59.663
lives for Christ, going to preach to the
Saracens, the Muslims, and they died.

00:05:59.663 --> 00:06:04.520
This inspired Saint Anthony
to follow the same path.

00:06:04.919 --> 00:06:11.610
He left the Augustinian order and
decided to join the Franciscan order.

00:06:11.610 --> 00:06:19.974
He had a very short formation and went
to Morocco himself to preach the gospel.

00:06:19.974 --> 00:06:27.223
However, it didn't turn out that way
because he fell ill very quickly.

00:06:27.223 --> 00:06:35.586
On his way back to Portugal, he
experienced a shipwreck due to a storm and

00:06:35.586 --> 00:06:39.490
ended up in Italy, specifically in Sicily.

00:06:40.490 --> 00:06:46.437
Here, that's a brief overview of his
life; we won't go further, but we'll

00:06:46.437 --> 00:06:49.836
return to the first part of his life.

00:06:49.836 --> 00:06:53.235
Saint Anthony was born
into a wealthy family.

00:06:53.235 --> 00:06:58.758
And the first thing we can notice
is the wealth he left behind.

00:06:58.758 --> 00:07:03.856
When we talk about wealth, it
somehow seems that in the Middle

00:07:03.856 --> 00:07:06.830
Ages it was much simpler than today.

00:07:07.390 --> 00:07:11.963
Today, however, it is harder
to leave behind a house we've

00:07:11.963 --> 00:07:14.874
inherited, a nice car, or a career.

00:07:14.874 --> 00:07:18.616
But actually, dear young
people, it's always the same.

00:07:18.616 --> 00:07:21.942
It's never easy to leave
behind material things.

00:07:21.942 --> 00:07:23.190
Why is that?

00:07:25.775 --> 00:07:29.568
Because material things
give us a sense of security.

00:07:29.568 --> 00:07:33.784
I have something to rely on,
something that protects me.

00:07:33.784 --> 00:07:36.735
But Jesus should be our only security.

00:07:37.595 --> 00:07:44.962
And we can go back to the Gospel and
see how the young man, the rich young

00:07:44.962 --> 00:07:47.996
man, asks Jesus what he should do.

00:07:47.996 --> 00:07:55.363
And Jesus tells him, if you want to be
perfect, go sell what you have and give

00:07:55.363 --> 00:08:01.864
to the poor, and you will have treasure
in heaven, then come and follow me.

00:08:01.864 --> 00:08:08.364
And then we also have where it says,
you cannot serve both God and wealth.

00:08:09.044 --> 00:08:14.804
Saint Anthony, when speaking about wealth
and interpreting this passage, says

00:08:14.804 --> 00:08:17.946
that serving wealth means rejecting God.

00:08:17.946 --> 00:08:24.753
The problem is not in having wealth,
which is even good and permissible,

00:08:24.753 --> 00:08:31.036
but in becoming a slave to that
wealth, which is greed itself.

00:08:31.036 --> 00:08:37.320
We can see many examples of saints
who decided to completely devote

00:08:37.320 --> 00:08:43.080
themselves to God, like Saint
Francis, who lived in radical poverty.

00:08:43.080 --> 00:08:48.458
And then there's Anthony, who even
before joining the Franciscans,

00:08:48.458 --> 00:08:54.375
by entering the Augustinian
order, also took a vow of poverty.

00:08:54.375 --> 00:09:00.830
I'll try to explain why wealth, or
better yet, attachments, are problematic.

00:09:00.830 --> 00:09:06.209
I assume that everyone here
wants to follow Jesus Christ.

00:09:06.209 --> 00:09:13.740
I assume that everyone wants to follow
the Lord, as Jesus has called us.

00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:18.860
And that you want to cooperate
with the Holy Spirit.

00:09:18.860 --> 00:09:23.899
Because the Holy Spirit is the
one who actualizes Jesus Christ.

00:09:23.899 --> 00:09:29.396
He makes Jesus' words, which are
recorded in the Gospel, present and

00:09:29.396 --> 00:09:33.060
tries to bring them closer to us today.

00:09:33.060 --> 00:09:39.473
And when we are under attachments,
let's say our life path is a journey

00:09:39.473 --> 00:09:45.428
and we walk, walk, walk, and we receive
an inspiration, like Saint Anthony

00:09:45.428 --> 00:09:51.841
received to go among the poor, to
preach to the Muslims, we receive an

00:09:51.841 --> 00:09:54.590
inspiration to go in another direction.

00:09:54.590 --> 00:10:00.240
We go straight, we get the inspiration
of the Holy Spirit to go left.

00:10:00.240 --> 00:10:07.101
And now, we would very easily take that
step to the left if we were, say, like

00:10:07.101 --> 00:10:09.927
Saint Francis, who had nothing behind him.

00:10:09.927 --> 00:10:15.173
But imagine carrying on your back, I
don't know, a house you're constantly

00:10:15.173 --> 00:10:18.402
thinking about, a car, a career, a job.

00:10:18.402 --> 00:10:22.842
But it's not just about material
things; there are also attachments,

00:10:22.842 --> 00:10:26.474
worries, problems, and some
people we are attached to.

00:10:26.515 --> 00:10:32.489
And the Holy Spirit says, let's
go left, but you can't go left.

00:10:32.489 --> 00:10:37.544
The Holy Spirit says, run, but
you can't run because you're

00:10:37.544 --> 00:10:39.382
dragging everything with you.

00:10:39.382 --> 00:10:45.816
I believe that when we are truly free
from everything, then you can go.

00:10:45.816 --> 00:10:51.331
And the Holy Spirit inspires
you to go, I don't know, to

00:10:51.331 --> 00:10:53.629
Germany, to America, to Africa.

00:10:53.629 --> 00:10:58.225
Here I am, Lord, send me,
says the prophet Isaiah.

00:11:02.785 --> 00:11:06.231
Let's go back to Fernando.

00:11:06.231 --> 00:11:14.502
Fernando was the original name of
Saint Anthony, and as an Augustinian

00:11:14.502 --> 00:11:23.463
monk, he had a very good, stable
life—something any monk would wish for.

00:11:23.463 --> 00:11:32.424
But when he heard the news about these
martyrs, his heart couldn't rest.

00:11:32.424 --> 00:11:36.560
He simply wasn't
satisfied with mediocrity.

00:11:37.200 --> 00:11:42.525
We don't want to belittle
his life up to that point.

00:11:42.525 --> 00:11:45.914
He simply realized that it wasn't enough.

00:11:45.914 --> 00:11:48.819
God wanted something different from him.

00:11:48.819 --> 00:11:54.144
Although he thought at that
moment that God wanted him to

00:11:54.144 --> 00:11:59.470
go to Morocco, he directed all
his efforts towards that goal.

00:11:59.470 --> 00:12:02.375
He had a desire for martyrdom.

00:12:02.375 --> 00:12:07.700
When we talk about martyrs,
they have existed since the very

00:12:07.700 --> 00:12:10.605
beginnings of the church, even today.

00:12:10.605 --> 00:12:14.478
Let's remember the apostles,
let's remember the first

00:12:14.478 --> 00:12:16.415
disciples like Saint Stephen.

00:12:16.415 --> 00:12:19.502
Everyone gave their blood for Christ.

00:12:19.502 --> 00:12:26.705
There were martyrs in our nation too, like
Blessed Aloysius Stepinac, who decided to

00:12:26.705 --> 00:12:30.821
give himself for God and for his people.

00:12:30.821 --> 00:12:36.480
But we also see this desire
in Saint Anthony, who wants

00:12:36.480 --> 00:12:39.053
to go like these martyrs.

00:12:39.053 --> 00:12:44.198
Interestingly, the word "martyrdom,"
if translated literally, means to give

00:12:44.198 --> 00:12:47.800
testimony, to be a witness for something.

00:12:49.370 --> 00:12:51.352
But are we witnesses today?

00:12:51.352 --> 00:12:57.301
We are afraid to make the sign of
the cross in the cafeteria, in case

00:12:57.301 --> 00:13:03.249
someone sees us, a friend might see
me, and then... What I mean to say

00:13:03.249 --> 00:13:08.008
is, people gave their lives for Christ
because they realized that Christ

00:13:08.008 --> 00:13:13.560
is love, they realized that Christ
lived for them, gave His life for us,

00:13:13.560 --> 00:13:16.335
died for us, and resurrected for us.

00:13:16.335 --> 00:13:19.905
And that is the strength
that carried them forward.

00:13:19.905 --> 00:13:23.806
And that's why they weren't
afraid to give their lives.

00:13:23.806 --> 00:13:25.757
But we, we are afraid.

00:13:25.757 --> 00:13:30.048
Today, we've entered a sphere, a
reality where everything seems difficult

00:13:30.048 --> 00:13:32.779
for us when it comes to Christ.

00:13:32.779 --> 00:13:37.071
And not just for Christ, we can
talk about different callings.

00:13:37.071 --> 00:13:39.802
Stjepan mentioned a lot in his sermon.

00:13:39.802 --> 00:13:45.264
We have the call to marriage, the call
to religious life, the priestly call.

00:13:45.264 --> 00:13:47.995
The call to charity, to serve others.

00:13:48.195 --> 00:13:50.787
It has become difficult for us.

00:13:50.787 --> 00:13:52.083
Why is that?

00:13:52.083 --> 00:13:53.380
I don't know.

00:13:53.380 --> 00:13:57.268
Somehow, we've become complacent,
especially we Christians in the

00:13:57.268 --> 00:13:59.861
West, in some kind of comfort.

00:13:59.861 --> 00:14:05.046
Everything is great, I'll come to
Holy Mass, which is truly wonderful,

00:14:05.046 --> 00:14:10.663
I'll pray, I'll come to the Divine
Mercy, a nice sermon, catechesis, then

00:14:10.663 --> 00:14:17.145
this adoration, I feel great, I feel
good, but is that all the Gospel is?

00:14:18.084 --> 00:14:20.574
Is the Gospel just about me feeling good?

00:14:20.574 --> 00:14:24.620
Of course it is, but that's not
the only aspect of the Gospel.

00:14:24.620 --> 00:14:28.977
We Christians often forget the part
of the Gospel that says, "Take up your

00:14:28.977 --> 00:14:34.579
cross and follow me." That part is a bit
harder for us, and we tend to forget it.

00:14:38.020 --> 00:14:42.641
Saint Anthony and other saints
ventured into the unknown with Jesus.

00:14:42.641 --> 00:14:45.582
We are all called to the same.

00:14:45.582 --> 00:14:48.103
We are all called to holiness.

00:14:48.103 --> 00:14:52.724
When we talk about Saint Anthony
and other saints, it somehow

00:14:52.724 --> 00:14:55.245
seems that they are far away.

00:14:55.245 --> 00:14:57.766
Their lives seem abstract to us.

00:14:57.766 --> 00:15:01.127
It's as if we only know their legends.

00:15:01.127 --> 00:15:07.009
But holiness is called upon by the
priest who preaches, by the first person

00:15:07.009 --> 00:15:13.311
sitting here in the pew, by the last
person, by the doctor, the miner, the

00:15:13.311 --> 00:15:17.933
worker, the student, the mother, the
father—everyone is called to holiness.

00:15:17.933 --> 00:15:23.395
Saint Anthony was not special, but
do you know what his uniqueness was?

00:15:23.455 --> 00:15:28.078
The courage, like that of all
other saints, to surrender to

00:15:28.078 --> 00:15:30.180
the workings of God's grace.

00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:33.122
To cooperate with God's
grace—that is holiness.

00:15:33.122 --> 00:15:34.804
To do God's will.

00:15:34.804 --> 00:15:39.848
And it's important that the
protagonist is the Holy Spirit, not us.

00:15:39.848 --> 00:15:44.051
And generally speaking, Saint
Anthony, let's say, goes, wants to

00:15:44.051 --> 00:15:48.675
go among the Saracens, the desire
for martyrdom, for missionary work.

00:15:48.675 --> 00:15:54.140
And when we talk about the church,
the nature of the church, as

00:15:54.140 --> 00:16:00.025
Lumen Gentium says, is that it is
missionary, it goes to meet the other.

00:16:00.025 --> 00:16:04.972
But when we talk about missions, we
don't immediately think of Africa,

00:16:04.972 --> 00:16:09.507
we don't immediately think of
South America or some poor areas,

00:16:09.507 --> 00:16:11.980
or those who haven't met Christ.

00:16:11.980 --> 00:16:16.515
We think about our everyday life,
bringing Christ wherever you are.

00:16:16.515 --> 00:16:20.638
Where you work, where you study,
daily bringing Christ, being

00:16:20.638 --> 00:16:22.700
a witness, being a martyr.

00:16:22.720 --> 00:16:22.894
But when we talk about missions, we
don't immediately think of Africa,

00:16:22.894 --> 00:16:23.054
we don't immediately think of
South America or some poor areas,

00:16:23.054 --> 00:16:23.141
or those who haven't met Christ.

00:16:23.141 --> 00:16:23.301
We think about our daily lives,
carrying Christ wherever you are.

00:16:23.301 --> 00:16:23.447
Where you work, where you study,
carrying Christ daily, being

00:16:23.447 --> 00:16:23.947
a witness, being a martyr.

00:16:26.240 --> 00:16:32.610
The last thing we want to focus on
is the failure of Saint Anthony.

00:16:32.610 --> 00:16:37.615
Imagine, he decided to join the
Franciscans, went through a brief

00:16:37.615 --> 00:16:40.345
formation, and now has the opportunity.

00:16:40.345 --> 00:16:46.714
He set off to Africa to preach his
life's dream and arrives on that

00:16:46.714 --> 00:16:49.444
foreign land, only to fall ill.

00:16:49.444 --> 00:16:56.724
We don't know what illness it was, but he
simply got sick and couldn't do anything.

00:16:56.724 --> 00:17:04.459
Now, try to put yourself in the shoes of
that young man who wants to give himself

00:17:04.459 --> 00:17:08.099
for Christ, but things didn't go his way.

00:17:08.339 --> 00:17:12.107
And what might such a
young man be thinking?

00:17:12.107 --> 00:17:17.131
Surely thoughts like these crossed
his mind: Did I make a mistake?

00:17:17.131 --> 00:17:19.224
Was this just a whim?

00:17:19.224 --> 00:17:21.317
Is this not God's will?

00:17:21.317 --> 00:17:23.829
But again, he rose above it.

00:17:23.829 --> 00:17:25.922
After that, he patiently endured.

00:17:25.922 --> 00:17:29.690
He ended up in Italy
where the news spread.

00:17:29.690 --> 00:17:33.457
But we often plan our lives the same way.

00:17:33.457 --> 00:17:38.481
I, for one, really like to have
everything planned out, to program

00:17:38.481 --> 00:17:41.830
my entire week, to have my own time.

00:17:41.830 --> 00:17:47.691
It makes me feel more at ease, it's
much simpler for me to function.

00:17:47.691 --> 00:17:53.552
But if we plan our entire lives in
advance—when I'll get married, when I'll

00:17:53.552 --> 00:17:58.994
achieve something, when I'll finish my
studies, when I'll get a good job—then

00:17:58.994 --> 00:18:01.925
somehow there's no room left for God.

00:18:02.975 --> 00:18:08.403
If we want God to lead our lives,
how do we solve that problem?

00:18:08.403 --> 00:18:10.730
What is the remedy for it?

00:18:10.730 --> 00:18:11.118
Faith.

00:18:11.118 --> 00:18:11.506
Faith.

00:18:11.506 --> 00:18:13.445
To let God guide us.

00:18:13.445 --> 00:18:17.322
I trust you, my God, that it will be good.

00:18:17.322 --> 00:18:22.364
Even though I might not see a
way out now, I believe, Jesus

00:18:22.364 --> 00:18:24.690
Christ, that you are with me.

00:18:24.690 --> 00:18:28.568
And truly, all the saints, all
those who surrendered themselves.

00:18:28.568 --> 00:18:33.997
I believe that if you have found yourself
in difficult situations, if you have

00:18:33.997 --> 00:18:40.590
let God act, let God lead you, the
light at the end of the tunnel has come.

00:18:42.670 --> 00:18:46.677
And that faith must be
active, not passive faith.

00:18:46.677 --> 00:18:52.467
Not the kind where you think
God is leading you so you don't

00:18:52.467 --> 00:18:55.139
need to do anything in life.

00:18:55.139 --> 00:18:57.365
Not that kind of faith.

00:18:57.365 --> 00:19:01.373
Saint Anthony says, our
faith is manifested in deeds.

00:19:01.373 --> 00:19:06.717
Anthony overcame this life's shipwreck
and after a few years, he preached.

00:19:06.717 --> 00:19:11.616
And when you think you are completely
broken, remember, often trials

00:19:11.616 --> 00:19:16.960
find us so difficult that they
push us into despair and breakdown.

00:19:17.550 --> 00:19:22.271
The Creator watches over our darkness
and once again disperses rays of

00:19:22.271 --> 00:19:25.026
light that were once withheld from us.

00:19:25.026 --> 00:19:29.747
Then, trust and hope will return
to you, granted by Divine mercy.

00:19:29.747 --> 00:19:35.256
Glory be to the Father, and to
the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.

00:19:35.256 --> 00:19:35.756
Here.

00:19:43.870 --> 00:19:46.558
We will conclude this catechesis here.

00:19:46.558 --> 00:19:49.246
Stjepan has given us a limit.

00:19:49.246 --> 00:19:55.071
I truly encourage you to study
the life of Saint Anthony and the

00:19:55.071 --> 00:19:58.207
lives of other saints on your own.

00:19:58.207 --> 00:20:04.479
Don't just rely on the legends you've
heard or some prayers, but delve into

00:20:04.479 --> 00:20:07.616
the essence of our saint, Saint Anthony.

00:20:07.616 --> 00:20:13.888
In the upcoming sessions, you will
be able to hear more about his life,

00:20:13.888 --> 00:20:17.025
which you have already seen as topics.

